doctitle.textblock: Intent To Grant Partially Exclusive Patent License; Federal Products Co.

action.textblock: Intent to grant partially exclusive patent license; Federal Products Company.

summary.textblock: The Department of the Navy hereby gives notice of its intent to grant to Federal Products Company a revocable, nonassignable, partially exclusive license in the United States to practice the Government-owned invention described in U.S. Patent Application Serial No. 130,480 entitled ``Magnetostrictive Linear Displacement Sensor, Angular Displacement Sensor, and Variable Resistor,'' filed October 1, 1993 in which the Government owns an undivided interest.

Anyone wishing to object to the grant of this license has 60 days from the date of this notice to file written objections along with supporting evidence, if any. Written objections are to be filed with the Office of Naval Research (ONR 00CC3), Ballston Tower One, Arlington, Virginia 22217-5660.

further.textblock: Mr. R.J. Erickson, Staff Patent Attorney, Office of Naval Research (ONR 00CC3), Ballston Tower One, 800 North Quincy Street, Arlington, Virginia 22217-5660, telephone (703) 696-4001.
